urls.title: Operators Ep 11: Andrew Munday (ex-DoorDash)
urls.description: Listen now (49 min) | Andrew Munday was the former Director of Operations and on the founding team of DoorDash. He has also started and run operations at several companies including Open, Future Fit, Pilaris, and currently Local Food Group which he co-founded. In this episode we talk about Andrew’s first job delivering pizzas, why he thinks hard work is the key to success, how a good COO aligns with the CEO, and several of his thoughts on hiring. He also shares what it was like in the early days at DoorDash, why he still thinks of it as the best deal of his life, and what a tough decision it was for him to leave.

Cover the low-level stuff that probably helps with prevention

text:
Happy to compete w/ the VCs treating quarantine as an extended vacation to Florida/Montana/Colorado

Happy to take the risk of socially distant walks for much higher fidelity conversation than your Zooms, <40 the risk is like skydiving

If you cant stomach some risk don't be a VC https://t.co/xnTOC2e1xC
@kareemsaleh @RamdaniRedouane Yes! I'll stop by in 3rd week of July
@sdamico Exactly
@Dragonsjet true! but if you want to get promoted you have to be near the decision-making, so if you go remote you are signaling you don't want to be ambitious
@Dragonsjet and they're willing to take a pay cut since they are competing with every engineer on Earth rather than just those that can make it to the bay area

Distanced walks w/ founders already proving to be 100x more useful than Zoom calls

Even w/o the ability to present a deck in a conference room or onto a laptop, the ability to connect & communicate is SOO much higher fidelity

Have done 10 in the past week & another 10 this week

@michaeljelly YC is good

Just being here physically 24/7 is the most important though, can't be replicated with anything else
